         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">27/11/66 ¶  ¶ I have to reply to a kind letter from you, dear Mr Bentham, received by last mail. ¶  You will receive the fascicles of Monopetaleae in rapid succession, though I shall not be able to se...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">66.11.27a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To George Bentham</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew Correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1858-1870, f. 245.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">27/11/66</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have to reply to a kind letter from you, dear Mr Bentham, received by last mail.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Presumably G. Bentham to M, 25 September 1866.</p>
               </note> You will receive the fascicles of <name key="Monopetaleae">Monopetaleae</name> in rapid succession, though I shall not be able to send any off until the jurors of the intercolonial Exhibition have done their work, and this will be at the beginning of 1867.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I presume you will be fully engaged on genera plantarum<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862-83).</p>
               </note> in the mean-while. I have so many additions to <name key="Coralliflorae">Coralliflorae</name> of late, that I cannot well send them off as they are and hence a little delay but otherwise the series of orders is almost ready.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <name key="Owenia%20cerasifera">Owenia cerasifera</name> turns out, while I now received flowers, to be <name key="Spondias%20pleiogyna">Spondias pleiogyna</name>
               <note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M had described <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Owenia%20cerasifera">Owenia cerasifera</name>
                     </seg> in B57.13.04, p. 305, and <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Spondias%20pleiogyna">Spondias pleiogyna</name>
                     </seg> in B64.02.01, p. 78.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I look forward with great interest to the conclusion of vol. III. In 1867 I shall be able to work more regularly on plants. I never had a year yet with so much extratoil &amp; besides other miseries<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A reference to the collapse of M's engagement to Rebecca Nordt? See Maroske (1997).</p>
               </note> as that now drawing to a close.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Let me hope that you preserve your health well,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">your regardful</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">You will receive Drummonds plants with mine.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Coralliflorae">Coralliflorae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Monopetaleae">Monopetaleae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Owenia%20cerasifera">Owenia cerasifera</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Spondias%20pleiogyna">Spondias pleiogyna</name>
            </p>
